    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Feby 8th 1851</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir, I have written<lb/> to <persName>Mr Saml Levy</persName>
                with reference to the amt.<lb/> due by <placeName>Augusta</placeName> congregation,
                for a sett of<lb/> Books. His reply has not been received as<lb/> yet, but
                    <persName>Mr Cohen</persName> tells me all will be right<lb/> the Congn having
                the means to pay.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As the <date>15th of Feby</date> is close at hand I<lb/> enclose you
                the circular. I regret to say that<lb/> it has received no addition of
                consequence<lb/> since I last reported.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">This has been owing to a number of<lb/> causes, the principal of
                which was my<lb/>
                <sic>sisters</sic> sickness. She (<persName>Sarah Ann</persName>) is<lb/> just
                recovering slowly from a severe attack<lb/> of <hi rend="underline">Confluent
                    Varioloid</hi>* with all its<lb/> painful and loathsome attendants.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have been barred from visiting in<lb/> consequence of the danger
                of infection, and<lb/> this together with my constant anxiety in<lb/> regard to her
                condition, has prevented me<lb/> from making applications for subscriptions.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Should you determine on the publication<lb/> of the Books, I will do
                whatever I can<lb/> to aid in their circulation.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Yrs &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Thos J Moïse</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Mother sends her regard.</p>
            <p>She is much broken by</p>
            <p>anxiety &amp; fatigue, but I</p>
            <p>hope she will speedily</p>
            <p>improve.</p>
            <p>*It is three weeks since she was taken</p>
        </body>
    </text>
